Article.ArticleTitle: [The chemotaxis effect of ampelopsin on the immunocytes].

AbstractText: To study the chemotaxis effect of ampelopsin with different concentration on monocytes and neutrophilic granulocytes.
Chemokinesis and chemotaxis tests were proceed in agarose gel comparing with chemokine IL-8 or MCP-1.

At 25.6 microg/ml or 51.2 microg/ml, ampelopsin could strongly enhance the migration of neutrophilic granulocytes and monocytes. The chemotaxis effect induced by 25.6 microg/ml of ampelopsin had no significant differences with that induced by 150 ng/ml of IL-8 or 50 ng/ml of MCP-1 (P > 0.05). At a concentration of 12.8 microg/ml, the chemokime effect of ampelopsin was more potent than that of 150 ng/ml of IL-8 or 100 ng/ml of MCP-1 (P < 0.05). Ampelopsin exerted a synergistic action with IL-8 or MCP-1 on its chemotaxis effect to neutrophilic granulocytes and monocytes.

Ampelopsin can strongly enhance the chemokinesis and chemotaxis effects of neutrophilic granulocytes and moncytes and exert a synergistic action with IL-8 or MCP-1 on its chemotaxis effect to neutrophilic granulocytes and monocytes.
